<subSubSection id="C343009923786052D2CEFAB8FDADA7F9" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6531223786053D2CEFAB8FBC9A38C" blockId="0.[747,1397,1345,1952]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
– The Katangan novelty 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D550FA9BFC29A03D" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[886,1006,1376,1400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D550FA9BFC29A03D" box="[886,1006,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related, morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D5BFFA85FBE6A0D3" authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[921,1057,1407,1430]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D5BFFA85FBE6A0D3" box="[921,1057,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D27BFA85FB24A0D3" box="[1117,1251,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
which differ mainly by the well developed upper lobes of their corolla, upper lobes which are lacking or extremely reduced in 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D332FA47FCC1A0B7" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D332FA47FCC1A0B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The other differences include spiny bracteoles (‘interpetiolar spines’ of various authors), calyx lobe margins provided with straight stiff-tipped teeth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D26DF9E3FB08A375" authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[1099,1231,1561,1584]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D26DF9E3FB08A375" box="[1099,1231,1561,1584]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D322F9E3FCC1A30B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
whereas soft bracteoles and upwards-curved soft-tipped teeth characterize the calyx lobe margins in 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D2EEF9ACFAFAA328" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[1224,1341,1621,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D2EEF9ACFAFAA328" box="[1224,1341,1621,1645]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The ecology and altitude ranges seem also to be different, as indicated below after the lists of the collected specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D37BF969FC96A38C" authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D37BF969FC96A38C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D5A3F948FBCFA38C" box="[901,1032,1714,1737]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6531223786052D537F92BFDADA7F9" blockId="0.[747,1397,1345,1952]" lastBlockId="1.[55,704,647,700]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D537F92BFC50A3AD" authorityName="C. B. Clarke (Clarke" authorityYear="1900" box="[785,919,1745,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyasensis">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D537F92BFC50A3AD" box="[785,919,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. nyasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D5E9F92BFB93A3AD" box="[975,1108,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. sunzuana</emphasis>
were put in sect. 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D33CF92AFAB3A3AD" baseAuthorityName="Balkwill &amp; Balkwill" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1306,1396,1744,1768]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D33CF92AFAB3A3AD" box="[1306,1396,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">Barleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC82EE323786053D528F914FBFAA242" box="[782,1085,1774,1799]" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill (1997)</bibRefCitation>
; this section is characterized by simple axillary inflorescences, toothed calyx lobes, corolla lobes in a 2 + 3 configuration, and two fertile stamens with three staminodes. 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123786053D5C5F8B1FB90A226" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[995,1111,1867,1891]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D5C5F8B1FB90A226" box="[995,1111,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be placed without any doubt in the same section. Another species of that section, 
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023786053D37BF890FCB2A2E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="82">B. bremekampii</emphasis>
Oberm., although morphologically distant from 
<taxonomicName id="4C59289123796052D611FD7DFF6AA7DA" authorityName="Dominique Champluvier" authorityYear="2011" box="[55,173,647,671]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Barleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="B92D8F0023796052D611FD7DFF6AA7DA" box="[55,173,647,671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="83">B. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has also extremely reduced upper corolla lobes (see drawing in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC82EE323796052D6C4FD5EFE3BA7F9" box="[226,508,676,700]" pageId="1" pageNumber="83" refId="ref9206" refString="Balkwill M. - J., Balkwill K. (1997) Delimitation and infrageneric classification of Barleria (Acanthaceae). Kew Bulletin 52: 535 - 573. [available at http: // www. jstor. org / pss / 4110286]" type="journal article">Balkwill &amp; Balkwill 1997</bibRefCitation>
: 556, B1).
</paragraph>
